{"_id":"0rwut77YISERpYwS","name":"Mute","type":"spell","img":"icons/svg/daze.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.helveczia.cleric-spells-2.0rwut77YISERpYwS"}},"system":{"level":"2","class":"cleric","range":"short","duration":"until absolution","area":"one target","save":"bravery","component":"","data":{"level":2,"class":"cleric"},"description":"<p class=\"p1\">This spell is a form of repentance meted out to sinners. They may not speak until they do penance, and receive absolution.</p>"},"ownership":{"default":0,"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"helveczia","systemVersion":"This is auto replaced","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672329180638,"modifiedTime":1672331706740,"lastModifiedBy":"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK"}}
{"_id":"1Dj1IejCcuzJOzHw","name":"Wine to Water","type":"spell","img":"icons/svg/daze.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.helveczia.cleric-spells-2.1Dj1IejCcuzJOzHw"}},"system":{"level":"2","class":"cleric","range":"short","duration":"15 minutes","area":"one group","save":"temptation","component":"","data":{"level":2,"class":"cleric"},"description":"<p class=\"p1\">This spell will quench even the most ferocious warrior&rsquo;s militancy. Unless they must fight for their life, they will lay down their arms, and contemplate life&rsquo;s matters for a quarter. This should be enough to run away, or convince them of the importance of peace; although it is better to run, for after the spell&rsquo;s span expires, they tend to return to their previous state of agitation.</p>"},"ownership":{"default":0,"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"helveczia","systemVersion":"This is auto replaced","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672329180638,"modifiedTime":1672331706740,"lastModifiedBy":"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK"}}
{"_id":"3LD6LaU8iyl1RMf4","name":"Protective Circle","type":"spell","img":"icons/svg/daze.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.helveczia.cleric-spells-2.3LD6LaU8iyl1RMf4"}},"system":{"level":"2","class":"cleric","range":"very short","duration":"until cockscrow","area":"a circle up to a chamber","save":"temptation","component":"","data":{"level":2,"class":"cleric"},"description":"<p class=\"p1\">This circle grants defence from the Devil, as well as other creatures and spirits against the natural order. The circle is drawn with chalk and holy water, one in one direction, and the other in the opposite (and those who know the ways of magic know which way for which). It either keeps its intended subjects outside, or it keeps them within &ndash; and they may only step through if they succeed at both saving throws &ndash; and even then for only one round. If they fail one save, they are thrown back; and if they fail both, they take 2d6 Hp damage. This is the only spell known to be used by both Clerics and Students.</p>\n<p class=\"p1\">Component: if it is used by Students, they will also require ground silver dust, which is endowed with the essences of the spheres in the correct lunar phase.</p>"},"ownership":{"default":0,"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"helveczia","systemVersion":"This is auto replaced","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672329180638,"modifiedTime":1672331706740,"lastModifiedBy":"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK"}}
{"_id":"92tsssphWntaEm4w","name":"Immaculate Gown","type":"spell","img":"icons/svg/daze.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.helveczia.cleric-spells-2.92tsssphWntaEm4w"}},"system":{"level":"2","class":"cleric","range":"-","duration":"30 minutes","area":"one person","save":"deftness","component":"","data":{"level":2,"class":"cleric"},"description":"<p class=\"p1\">The gown, or robes of the subject appear especially clean and devoid of any dirt. And those who would touch them with malice, by hand or object, will be burned for 2d6 Hp, plus 1 more per level. Even those who save suffer half the damage. However, it is useless against missile weapons.</p>"},"ownership":{"default":0,"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"helveczia","systemVersion":"This is auto replaced","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672329180639,"modifiedTime":1672331706740,"lastModifiedBy":"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK"}}
{"_id":"A8j9rRoLbZdtZjzi","name":"Protection from Arrows","type":"spell","img":"icons/svg/daze.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.helveczia.cleric-spells-2.A8j9rRoLbZdtZjzi"}},"system":{"level":"2","class":"cleric","range":"-","duration":"half an hour","area":"around oneself","save":"-","component":"","data":{"level":2,"class":"cleric"},"description":"<p class=\"p1\">The luminous halo which surrounds the honest souls will stop arrows, bullets and thrown rocks, although heavier things like cannonballs or grenades are only reduced in power, by one point per level.</p>"},"ownership":{"default":0,"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"helveczia","systemVersion":"This is auto replaced","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672329180639,"modifiedTime":1672331706740,"lastModifiedBy":"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK"}}
{"_id":"BmaTwGwJ6XuZPWX8","name":"Miraculous Chalice","type":"spell","img":"icons/svg/daze.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.helveczia.cleric-spells-2.BmaTwGwJ6XuZPWX8"}},"system":{"level":"2","class":"cleric","range":"short","duration":"until cockscrow","area":"one group","save":"-","component":"","description":"<p class=\"p1\">The likeness of a splendid chalice appears above the darkness-shrouded campsite, and this vision will keep both enemies and beasts from the resting company.</p>\n<p class=\"p1\">Everyone will recover +2 Hp over this time. The spell is broken only if an evil heart contemplating treachery hides among them.</p>"},"ownership":{"default":0,"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"helveczia","systemVersion":"This is auto replaced","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672329180639,"modifiedTime":1672331706740,"lastModifiedBy":"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK"}}
{"_id":"CQxqLL9e6XlKKJMg","name":"Faithful Flower","type":"spell","img":"icons/svg/daze.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.helveczia.cleric-spells-2.CQxqLL9e6XlKKJMg"}},"system":{"level":"2","class":"cleric","range":"-","duration":"seven days","area":"one target","save":"-","component":"","description":"<p class=\"p1\">This modest but nice flower is usually given to those who embark on a journey, as it will glow like a candle at night, and in the morning, its bearer will always heal 2 extra Hp from resting, and another if they are in a state of high Virtue. In a great need, it can be transferred to another, but never taken back. Should it come into sinful hands, someone with low Virtue: it immediately turns dark and wilts.</p>"},"ownership":{"default":0,"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"helveczia","systemVersion":"This is auto replaced","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672329180639,"modifiedTime":1672331706740,"lastModifiedBy":"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK"}}
{"_id":"D5M3Uz0CygZJw5o1","name":"Eager Herald","type":"spell","img":"icons/svg/daze.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.helveczia.cleric-spells-2.D5M3Uz0CygZJw5o1"}},"system":{"level":"2","class":"cleric","range":"long","duration":"within 1 minute","area":"around oneself/village","save":"bravery","component":"","data":{"level":2,"class":"cleric"},"description":"<p class=\"p1\">Evil often does its work at night, and its work often lasts till cockcrow. But if this cock were to speak early, the plans might be unfinished &ndash; and so, this spell immediately calls the dawn&rsquo;s messenger, and with it sunrise. It is a real miracle, but should only be used by those who are sure of its usefulness: for every hour miraculously received, the Cleric must later sleep an entire week; and if the spell was used for an evil purpose, so many years.</p>"},"ownership":{"default":0,"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"helveczia","systemVersion":"This is auto replaced","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672329180639,"modifiedTime":1672331706741,"lastModifiedBy":"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK"}}
{"_id":"EtHlJ9Q4zw2Dw2iP","name":"Cornucopia","type":"spell","img":"icons/svg/daze.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.helveczia.cleric-spells-2.EtHlJ9Q4zw2Dw2iP"}},"system":{"level":"2","class":"cleric","range":"-","duration":"mealtime","area":"-","save":"-","component":"","data":{"level":2,"class":"cleric"},"description":"<p class=\"p1\">The most varied delicacies and drinks are laid before a company of up to three persons per level, who can feast on this abundance to their heart&rsquo;s content.</p>"},"ownership":{"default":0,"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"helveczia","systemVersion":"This is auto replaced","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672329180640,"modifiedTime":1672331706741,"lastModifiedBy":"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK"}}
{"_id":"Mjsrk41vr4zTxMBV","name":"Prohibited Passages","type":"spell","img":"icons/svg/daze.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.helveczia.cleric-spells-2.Mjsrk41vr4zTxMBV"}},"system":{"level":"2","class":"cleric","range":"short","duration":"one day","area":"a cross, and around","save":"temptation","component":"","data":{"level":2,"class":"cleric"},"description":"<p class=\"p1\">It is used on a cross, whose shadow afterwards no sinner can pass; only those who have high Virtue. Even approaching it requires a saving throw. If someone were to force themselves, or touch the cross, a heavy burden crushes them for 3d6 Hp damage, and another per level. On characters with average Virtue, this counts as knockout damage, but the more sinful will be crushed to death.</p>"},"ownership":{"default":0,"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"helveczia","systemVersion":"This is auto replaced","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672329180640,"modifiedTime":1672331706741,"lastModifiedBy":"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK"}}
{"_id":"O0DDuAPJcgEkycDS","name":"Withdraw Poison","type":"spell","img":"icons/svg/daze.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.helveczia.cleric-spells-2.O0DDuAPJcgEkycDS"}},"system":{"level":"2","class":"cleric","range":"touch","duration":"one week","area":"one target","save":"bravery","component":"","data":{"level":2,"class":"cleric"},"description":"<p class=\"p1\">It removes the most diverse kinds of poisons from food, drink, the poisoned, but even poisonous plants and animals &ndash; turning even the adder into a harmless animal (for it will bite, but cannot sting with its tongue). The poison can collect anew, but for a week, they will surely be harmless. The remaining poison can be put to use as required, since in many forms, it can become the best kind of medicine.</p>"},"ownership":{"default":0,"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"helveczia","systemVersion":"This is auto replaced","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672329180640,"modifiedTime":1672331706741,"lastModifiedBy":"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK"}}
{"_id":"RX5gUjSwsBFriKEZ","name":"Lantern of the Lost","type":"spell","img":"icons/svg/daze.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.helveczia.cleric-spells-2.RX5gUjSwsBFriKEZ"}},"system":{"level":"2","class":"cleric","range":"-","duration":"instantaneous","area":"-","save":"-","component":"","data":{"level":2,"class":"cleric"},"description":"<p class=\"p1\">It is a great relief for those who have been lost or found themselves in peril, for a heavenly sign or stroke of inspiration will show them how they might escape from their predicament. It only works if the company includes at least one person of high Virtue.</p>"},"ownership":{"default":0,"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"helveczia","systemVersion":"This is auto replaced","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672329180640,"modifiedTime":1672331706741,"lastModifiedBy":"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK"}}
{"_id":"WPRclzetPiS15LaE","name":"Hands of St Laurence","type":"spell","img":"icons/svg/daze.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.helveczia.cleric-spells-2.WPRclzetPiS15LaE"}},"system":{"level":"2","class":"cleric","range":"-","duration":"quarter of an hour","area":"cleric and companions","save":"-","component":"","data":{"level":2,"class":"cleric"},"description":"<p class=\"p1\">The Cleric is not burned by fire, nor choked by smoke; and if they were hit by a flaming beam in a burning building, they can cast it aside as if they had Strength: 18. This is only valid for natural fires lit by normal means, and not salamanders, alchemical mixtures, the dragons of legend or the other fires of Hell &ndash; although even then, the damage is halved.</p>"},"ownership":{"default":0,"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"helveczia","systemVersion":"This is auto replaced","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672329180640,"modifiedTime":1672331706741,"lastModifiedBy":"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK"}}
{"_id":"Y8bD7uKUw7ZfWmSf","name":"Stumble","type":"spell","img":"icons/svg/daze.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.helveczia.cleric-spells-2.Y8bD7uKUw7ZfWmSf"}},"system":{"level":"2","class":"cleric","range":"touch","duration":"until cockscrow","area":"one doorway","save":"deftness","component":"","data":{"level":2,"class":"cleric"},"description":"<p class=\"p1\">Thus, one can draw a line before a door, gate or other doorway with holy water, and this threshold will make the sinful stumble. Those who come under the burden of sins, with low Virtue, shall fall on their face and start to swear; those who would come to steal will break their leg; and those who contemplate murder will break their necks.</p>"},"ownership":{"default":0,"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"helveczia","systemVersion":"This is auto replaced","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672329180641,"modifiedTime":1672331706741,"lastModifiedBy":"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK"}}
{"_id":"bsc0Zkkw5JkyDwf9","name":"Anathema","type":"spell","img":"icons/svg/daze.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.helveczia.cleric-spells-2.bsc0Zkkw5JkyDwf9"}},"system":{"level":"2","class":"cleric","range":"short","duration":"quarter of an hour","area":"one group","save":"temptation","component":"","data":{"level":2,"class":"cleric"},"description":"<p class=\"p1\">Those who hear the word of excommunication will be barred from both the Cleric and a holy site: they may neither approach nor attack them unless they themselves are endangered by either. It is only useful against those with average or low Virtue, but the latter save at -2.</p>"},"ownership":{"default":0,"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"helveczia","systemVersion":"This is auto replaced","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672329180641,"modifiedTime":1672331706741,"lastModifiedBy":"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK"}}
{"_id":"dSON1UYmV1Ce6afv","name":"Miraculous Medicine","type":"spell","img":"icons/svg/daze.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.helveczia.cleric-spells-2.dSON1UYmV1Ce6afv"}},"system":{"level":"2","class":"cleric","range":"touch","duration":"instantaneous","area":"one person","save":"-","component":"","data":{"level":2,"class":"cleric"},"description":"<p class=\"p1\">It cures certain afflictions, e.g. sickness and poison, although it can only offer temporary relief for the plague, gout and the common cold. Furthermore, it returns 2d6 Hp plus 1 per two caster levels. The tears of holy icons have similar powers if they are used to cleanse the body.</p>"},"ownership":{"default":0,"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"helveczia","systemVersion":"This is auto replaced","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672329180641,"modifiedTime":1672331706741,"lastModifiedBy":"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK"}}
{"_id":"g2W2z9rTzyTaOmZ6","name":"Aversion","type":"spell","img":"icons/svg/daze.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.helveczia.cleric-spells-2.g2W2z9rTzyTaOmZ6"}},"system":{"level":"2","class":"cleric","range":"medium","duration":"instantaneous","area":"a spell and caster","save":"deftness","component":"","data":{"level":2,"class":"cleric"},"description":"<p class=\"p1\">There is no spell more simple. If magic is sent the caster&rsquo;s way, one word can turn it back and let them have it. They can roll a Deftness save, but whether they make it or not it is the originally intended targets who are truly saved.</p>"},"ownership":{"default":0,"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"helveczia","systemVersion":"This is auto replaced","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672329180641,"modifiedTime":1672331706741,"lastModifiedBy":"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK"}}
{"_id":"h9cruMZU6v8zpY6J","name":"Faith's Mallet","type":"spell","img":"icons/svg/daze.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.helveczia.cleric-spells-2.h9cruMZU6v8zpY6J"}},"system":{"level":"2","class":"cleric","range":"medium","duration":"quarter of an hour","area":"around oneself/courtyard","save":"-","component":"","data":{"level":2,"class":"cleric"},"description":"<p class=\"p1\">A spell meant against beasts, unbelievers and devilry, it calls into being a two-handed mallet, which flies through the air by the character&rsquo;s commands. It can attack with the same skill as the Cleric, and cause very heavy wounds (1d10 plus Strength bonus). If the chosen foe is defeated, it can be sent to another, but it will not part from a selected target for any reason. It will not attack a Christian, but there is a 1:2 probability it will attack a Calvinist. It is said, the same has been experienced vice versa when encountering the deviltry of Calvinist preachers, who have no doubt reproduced the effects of this most holy instrument with the Devil&rsquo;s inspiration and tools.</p>"},"ownership":{"default":0,"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"helveczia","systemVersion":"This is auto replaced","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672329180641,"modifiedTime":1672331706741,"lastModifiedBy":"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK"}}
{"_id":"hQCOWgv08seSieqa","name":"Guardian Sword","type":"spell","img":"icons/svg/daze.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.helveczia.cleric-spells-2.hQCOWgv08seSieqa"}},"system":{"level":"2","class":"cleric","range":"touch","duration":"until defeated","area":"little space","save":"-","component":"","data":{"level":2,"class":"cleric"},"description":"<p class=\"p1\">It raises a sword glowing with holy light and floating in the air to protect a place. If an interloper &ndash; anyone with low or average Virtue, or approaching with bad intentions &ndash; would disturb it, the weapon attacks, and fights them like a knight. The sword is level 3+1 (from fifth level, 4+2), has AC 15, and inflicting 1d10+3 Hp damage. This spell is only kept by the followers of Saint Stephen or Saint Ladislaus of Hungary,</p>\n<p class=\"p1\">and they will only give it to those who have earned it.</p>"},"ownership":{"default":0,"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"helveczia","systemVersion":"This is auto replaced","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672329180642,"modifiedTime":1672331706741,"lastModifiedBy":"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK"}}
{"_id":"t8FyeMejLQK9YARb","name":"Stone Loaf","type":"spell","img":"icons/svg/daze.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.helveczia.cleric-spells-2.t8FyeMejLQK9YARb"}},"system":{"level":"2","class":"cleric","range":"-","duration":"very long","area":"-","save":"-","component":"","data":{"level":2,"class":"cleric"},"description":"<p class=\"p1\">It creates a loaf of bread made of granite stone, but someone who has high Virtue can eat it with a good appetite without any ill effects. What other use it could possess, is not told by the monks who are keeping it.</p>"},"ownership":{"default":0,"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"helveczia","systemVersion":"This is auto replaced","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672329180642,"modifiedTime":1672331706741,"lastModifiedBy":"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK"}}
